127
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:33,990
What is this?

128
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:43,200
Yes, Mr. Lee.

129
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,010
I just came back from an overseas business trip.

130
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:46,270
I just received the call.

131
00:09:46,270 --> 00:09:47,960
 Take care and come. 

132
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,870
Okay. B-But...

133
00:09:50,870 --> 00:09:53,080
why is he calling us in?

134
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:55,890
 An article was published today... 

135
00:10:08,830 --> 00:10:10,600
There are no issues with Wind.

136
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,550
Why did such an article get published?

137
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:15,000
- Was there an issue? 
 - I'm not sure.

138
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,780
Since they asked me to pay back my debt,

139
00:10:17,780 --> 00:10:20,490
I sold Construction and paid them back.

140
00:10:20,490 --> 00:10:23,110
Now, the stock prices are flipping out.

141
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:27,550
Look.

142
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:34,210
They say Sanin will collapse because of Wind.

143
00:10:38,450 --> 00:10:42,480
Wind was a division we were already carrying.

144
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,950
Then...

145
00:10:44,850 --> 00:10:47,820
why haven't we listed it yet?

146
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:54,260
An IPO depends on market conditions,

147
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:57,650
but the current atmosphere wasn't great.

148
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:02,020
Hey,

149
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:06,530
