150
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:08,010
Tell me.

151
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:11,870
You're right.

152
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:13,520
Yes?

153
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:17,720
CEO Oh Chi Yeong is here.

154
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,000
Come in.

155
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,490
Yes, Chairman.

156
00:11:20,490 --> 00:11:23,080
I got back from my overseas business trip yesterday

157
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:25,100
so I received your call late. I'm sorry.

158
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,760
- On a business trip? 
 - Yes.

159
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:28,900
You know our resort in Saipan?

160
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:33,040
We're developing a tour package there right now.

161
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:36,270
These days, a lot of people travel abroad.

162
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:38,340
- Take a seat. 
 - Yes, yes.

163
00:11:39,290 --> 00:11:41,220
Was it fun?

164
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:43,380
- Pardon? 
 - Did you have fun

165
00:11:43,380 --> 00:11:46,050
traveling overseas after

166
00:11:46,050 --> 00:11:48,730
letting Wind sink like this?

167
00:11:48,730 --> 00:11:50,310
Well...

168
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,450
- Wind is my— 
 - Chairman.

169
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:55,270
Listing is my responsibility.

170
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:56,900
It would've...

171
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:59,700
- It would've been fine if you did well. 
 - Well,

172
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:03,830
after COVID, the leisure market was terrible.

173
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:06,800
You! Are you making that excuse again?

174
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:11,340
- You! What did I tell you? Well? 
 - Pardon?

175
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:14,070
Why don't you go to the Han River right now?

176
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:16,740
There are bicycles everywhere!

177
00:12:16,740 --> 00:12:18,510
Chairman...

178
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:30,670
You're the CEO,

179
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,690
but you're blaming others?

180
00:12:33,570 --> 00:12:35,450
Do CEOs...

181
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:38,410
blame others?

182
00:12:38,410 --> 00:12:39,920
Well?

183
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,790
I'm sorry.

184
00:13:33,470 --> 00:13:35,550
Is CEO Oh in charge of Wind?

185
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:37,720
Yes. I think he came to HQ.

186
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,920
To see the chairman?

187
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:40,780
Yes, I believe so.

188
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:42,860
I thought he might call for you as well, Mr. Ha.

189
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:44,870
Okay, okay.

190
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:48,200
- Hurry and get ready. 
 - Okay.

191
00:13:48,260 --> 00:13:53,680
The chairman just lost his temper.

192
00:13:53,680 --> 00:13:55,080
Don't take it too personally.

193
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,880
How is Wind my responsibility?

194
00:13:58,510 --> 00:14:02,200
Honestly, I never said I'd take it on.

195
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,700
Mr. Ha acquired it, and someone else manages it.

196
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:09,100
CEO Oh, let's talk about it downstairs.

197
00:14:11,540 --> 00:14:14,190
CEO Oh, working hard?

198
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:29,200
You're here.

199
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,530
- Would you like a cup of coffee? 
 - Coffee...

200
00:14:31,530 --> 00:14:34,170
- I'm okay. 
 - Please take a seat.

201
00:14:49,270 --> 00:14:52,560
I tried to get Wind listed

202
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:55,230
but received a negative report.

203
00:14:55,230 --> 00:14:56,820
That's why we put it on hold.

204
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:58,760
Why? Wind was doing so well.

205
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:01,410
After Wind was acquired in 2015,

206
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:03,000
it went through some ups and downs.

207
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,530
But from 2021 to last year,

208
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:08,500
its sales grew by 30% every year.

209
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:10,700
My goodness.

210
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,500
Bicycles are not like IT.

211
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,760
How could it grow by 30%?

212
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:17,450
Many of my friends belong to cycling clubs.

213
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:18,970
Exactly. It was impressive.

214
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:22,210
Looking back now, it benefited from COVID.

215
00:15:22,210 --> 00:15:25,610
At the time, there was much optimism about leisure.

216
00:15:25,610 --> 00:15:27,990
It was my mistake, really.

217
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:31,210
Since cycling was an individual sport

218
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:33,330
without face-to-face contact,

219
00:15:33,330 --> 00:15:36,660
I didn't realize it benefited from COVID

220
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:39,400
and thought it would grow further.

221
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:42,170
So I waited.

222
00:15:42,170 --> 00:15:45,410
But that's not your fault, Mr. Lee.

223
00:15:48,220 --> 00:15:51,750
I should've reported it to the chairman sooner,

224
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:54,670
but I hesitated to tell him.

225
00:15:55,340 --> 00:15:58,250
I think Mr. Lee made a mistake, Chairman.

226
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,920
He should've listed it when it was trending up.

227
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,800
I feel it's a bit too late now.

228
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,580
Enough about Mr. Lee.

229
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:09,190
You tell me what you think.

230
00:16:09,190 --> 00:16:11,410
In my opinion,

231
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:14,710
stopping the put option is most important.

232
00:16:14,710 --> 00:16:16,450
And?

233
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:19,250
How about we persuade PPF?

234
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:20,540
Do you want to do it?

235
00:16:20,540 --> 00:16:23,120
Yes, I'll try meeting with them.

236
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:25,380
Then make them sign,

237
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:27,540
saying they won't exercise the put option.

238
00:16:27,540 --> 00:16:30,250
- Pardon? 
 - If they just say they won't

239
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:31,770
but decide to do so later,

240
00:16:31,770 --> 00:16:34,670
I'd be the only one getting kicked out.

241
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,700
There's no way.

242
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:43,150
Then you are also saying Wind is hopeless.

243
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:45,010
Yes, Chairman.

244
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:57,440
Why is he so afraid?

245
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,950
Pardon?

246
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:06,210
Can't Mr. Ha just go to PPF and persuade them?

247
00:17:06,210 --> 00:17:07,440
They're close.

248
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:10,460
If PPF was going to help us, they would've already.

249
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:12,840
"We are joint partners with Sanin."

250
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:14,270
That's all they had to say,

251
00:17:14,270 --> 00:17:16,600
and the stock price wouldn't have plummeted.

252
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:18,840
But they're pretending not to know anything.

253
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:21,920
Now that Mr. Ha has lost Construction

254
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:24,790
and has no influence over PPF,

255
00:17:24,790 --> 00:17:26,840
he has nothing, right?

256
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:41,230
CEO Oh was crying.

257
00:17:41,230 --> 00:17:42,510
Pardon?

258
00:17:42,510 --> 00:17:44,190
For failing to list Wind,

259
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:47,030
he got yelled at by the chairman and was crying.

260
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:53,640
Then how about you go and talk to PPF?

261
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,830
I offered to do so,

262
00:17:55,830 --> 00:17:58,000
but the chairman says to let it be.

263
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,700
He said just break it this time and move on

264
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,050
whether the listing happens or not.

265
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:05,340
W-Wind?

266
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:07,550
Whether it's Wind or whatever else.

267
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:10,500
He was furious.

268
00:18:11,110 --> 00:18:13,180
I guess you met with the chairman.

269
00:18:13,180 --> 00:18:15,570
Yes, just now.

270
00:18:15,570 --> 00:18:18,830
Wind should've been listed a long time ago.

271
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:20,200
What's the point now?

272
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:22,780
I know, right? Now that COVID is over,

273
00:18:22,780 --> 00:18:25,420
people with money are busy traveling abroad,

274
00:18:25,420 --> 00:18:27,480
and those without are busy making ends meet.

275
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:29,910
Who's going to ride a bike these days?

276
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:32,560
CEO Oh must've wanted to cry.

277
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,040
He didn't just want to cry.

278
